The paper focuses on index modulation schemes in wireless communications, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The use of compressive sensing based reconstruction algorithms for signal detection suggests a possible connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the exploration of indexing opportunities in load modulated multiantenna systems suggests a possible connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
